  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nPending contact requests are not shown when the user doesn't have at least one mutual contact.\r\n\r\n<table>\r\n  <thead>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <th></th>\r\n      <th></th>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </thead>\r\n  <tbody>\r\n    <tr>\r\n      <td><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/208757150-01cef681-cbe8-4263-8da3-2e1c644f0b0f.png\" height=\"500\" /></td>\r\n      <td><img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/208756528-1c2b633a-dd67-4e45-87d7-fbf3a0a83600.png\" height=\"500\" /></td>\r\n    </tr>\r\n  </tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nThe user should see the pending contact requests section if there's one or more pending requests, regardless of the total amount of mutual contacts in their contact list.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/46027/208757888-6c630efa-dbde-43e3-b503-616393313953.png\" height=\"500\" />\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1. Create account A\r\n2. As B, send a contact request to A\r\n3. Open the `Messages` screen, `Contacts` tab.\r\n4. Verify there's no *Pending contacts* section, but the Activity Center shows the request.\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: nightly \r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n\r\n",
